parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes fail to engage
the vehicle rolls forward despite pressing the brake pedal
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels excessively
the brake warning indicator flashes
the emergency braking system deploys unnecessarily (phantom braking).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive travel of the brake pedal can cause the driver to lose confidence in the braking system, leading to delayed or incomplete braking, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels excessively
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake warning indicator flashes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unnecessary deployment of the emergency braking system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The emergency braking system deploys unnecessarily
the brake warning indicator flashes
the vehicle comes to a complete stop without any objects in front of it.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Distortion and Wavy/Orange Peel Appearance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The distorted windshield can cause visual discomfort, dizziness, and impaired vision, which can lead to accidents or affect the driver's ability to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The windshield has a wavy/orange peel appearance
distorted view
blurry vision
dizzying effect
and impaired vision when looking at objects in front of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper can reduce visibility during rain or other weather conditions, increasing the risk of accidents or accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wiper fails to clear water from the windshield
leaving the driver with impaired visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to safety risks, especially in unfamiliar areas, and potentially causing accidents or stranding.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reading is non-linear
the fuel gauge reading is erroneous
the fuel level is unpredictable
running out of fuel unexpectedly
fuel gauge fluctuates or jumps erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Unintended Acceleration with ActiveSense System Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the driver is attempting to brake or maneuver in tight spaces.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly and rapidly accelerates while the driver is pressing the brake pedal

often resulting in collision or near-collision incidents. The dashboard may display warnings such as "ActiveSense system malfunction" or "ActiveSense advanced safety and driver support system may not operate correctly."

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the blind spot monitoring system can cause unnecessary alerts, distractions, and potentially lead to accidents due to the driver's reliance on the system. the rear cross traffic warning system fails to activate
the systems do not function as intended
false warnings or alerts are displayed.

symptoms: The blind spot monitoring system alerts constantly or unnecessarily
the system does not function as intended
false warnings or alerts are displayed.
